,Not Recommended,230050,9888747,"Posted: 21 April, 2014",all,SirCrest,"At first I thought the jokes were kind of charming in a sense because it was kind of subtle, but by the end it was forced to the point of not even being funny. Sure, as someone who is involved in games a lot I recognized the reference, but it felt like it was relying on the puncline alone to be the joke.This game plays like a typical platformer like mario, except it doesn't do a good job. The entire thing is platforming and it's very floaty and slidy. For me, it was not really a pleasure to play. It was simply a game I wanted to finsh because people told me it was short.The concept of finding all of the coins is fine for buying the next item to unlock the next area but, but margins of what is available and what is not means you're searching the entire level of any single missing coins. This causes tons of worthless backtracking looking for hidden sides of walls trying to get that next amount of coins. The snow area was the greatest offender in this regard. You're playing it for the jokes and humor, but you have to get past all the annoying stuff to get to it.Sure, for the price on or off sale it's good value for the time, but even for maybe an hour or so of solid gameplay it's incredibly boring and full of filler. You're playing it for the references. Which aren't worth it. If you want a good experience, play the first chapter and uninstall it.If you want jokes about the games industry go read the hundreds of comics about games online. You'll be more entertained. An ironically annoying game is still an annoying game."
