,Recommended,230050,10939738,"Posted: 29 June, 2014",all,fo_ruM✨,"""YOU SHOULD TRY THE ORIGINAL DLC QUEST FIRST! OR DON'T. I'M A MESSAGE BOX, NOT A COP.""Game, which is adventure of Bobby Kotick and his Activision, EA and their rise of microtransactions, greed and illness of gaming industry, and publishers and their managers who aren't managers, but money-hunters. They are more like shephards whose sheeps are eating download-able content than green.Going Loud Studio shows us, and describes us, how nowadays gaming industry works, with the satire and humor and only with that, because there're plenty of articles, showing the truth, and we can't laugh about it. DLC Quest shows us the truth, and we can and we'll laugh about it so hard.Type of games, which's doing this and having hidden messages from devs and designers in-game, are halfway to be great rated. No wonders, it's like that.Dialogues are well-written, game-design is solid like Solid Snake, same goes with level-design. In game, we've got two modes to play - DLC Quest and Live Freemium or Die.DLC Quest is basically main campaign and LFoD is consequence, with way more interesting and gripping world, voyage and level-design. Wall Jump is more entertaining than Double Jump which's in main campaign.Game has full-controller support (1 stick and 1 button) and I'd recommend you using it, than keyboard.Game could be little bit longer (1 hour per each mod on the first run / speedrun can be done with everything collected under 20 mins) but sometimes less is more, and this game confirms it, and the whole situation in gaming industry was described here more than well.Bonus Point: Making Fun of DLC PolicyRating: 9/10"
