,Not Recommended,230050,8770832,"Posted: 19 January, 2014",all,imac2much,"And stay even further away from this game.  I'm noticing a trend of smaller titles whose selling points are their tongue-in-cheek critique of gaming tropes and cliches; when done well, these games can be very memorable.  Unfortunately, many games (like Evoland, DLC Quest and to a lesser degree, Retro City Rampage) forget to make the core game fun too.  Having unenjoyable game mechanics for the sake of reminding the player that said mechanics are not enjoyable is not a good idea.  In the end, the player is STILL not having fun, with the added insult of the developer rubbing it in his or her face."
