76561198107679514,Recommended,230050,11019136,"Posted: 2 July, 2014",all,Shadowcrunch,"This game is fun! Lighthearted and humorous, DLC Quest pokes fun at the ridiculous amounts of DLC in games these days, while also being a solid and enjoyable platformer. I had seriously planned to not like this game because ""yay! Another platformer where you collect coins!"", and based on the graphics I was expecting something like a flash browser game with horrible controls and an unfinished feel. My plans were ruined!You do collect coins, but that's as far as my expectations made it. I found the controls to be tight, with a minimal amount of slide after letting off a key. Any times I missed a jump and fell, I felt it was more my fault than any fault of sloppy controls. The graphics are retro-ish and very fitting for the style and atmosphere of the game. The sound also fits nicely. The satirical finger-pointing at the DLC market, and the humorous comments from the characters, round out a quick and FUN little platform game!OH, I will add that the first time I ran this game, I set a widescreen resolution in the options, and the first character I talked to, I got my first Windows 8 blue screen. I don't know for sure this game was the problem, but the BSOD was ""DRIVER_IRQL_NOT_LESS_OR_EQUAL"" and a quick google search told me this error happens with bad drivers or bad applications. After a reboot, I started the game and changed resolutions, and have not had a problem since."
