,Recommended,230050,24599954,"Posted: 29 July, 2016",all,hardAtwork,"DLC Quest is a video game that makes fun of microtransactions.Like this review?  Buy the full version to access the reviewer's commentary, fully revealing his thoughts on the game!  $59.99.That joke aside, DLC Quest truly is a game which satirizes the practice of games using downloadable content to rake in the Benjamins, so to speak.  Now, if you're wondering, no, this game does not actually use downloadable content in it that requires you to actually pay real life, ""earned from your job"" money.  That would be redundant.No, rather, DLC Quest has you collect in-game coins to purchase DLC that is required to progress in the game.  Some of the ""DLC"" you collect is the ability to walk in a certain direction, and another one goes as far as to require you to buy it if you want to double-jump.  Along your journey to buy them all, you'll encounter several video game references as you stride across this land of imaginary paywalls.  It is a hilarious satire game, but as it stands, if you do not get or like the humor, it is pretty much not worth your money if a satire based on the practices of downloadable content are not up to your liking.But if you are intrigued, great!  It is not anything too revolutionary gameplay wise, but hopefully it will give you quite the chuckle then and there, and I highly recommend it to anyone who is invested in the video game community or industry."
