76561198110039295,Recommended,230050,26551489,"Posted: 11 November, 2016",all,Mad_phoenix,"This satirical game is about DLC. If that wasn't obvious from the title, well, this game may not be for you. Anyways, in this game, you play as, well, a character. Just a generic sprite in a empty world. That's right, it's completely empty besides a princess and an evil arch-villain. You have to buy DLC to do literally everything in this game, including walking left. This said, the DLC purchasing is what gives it its charm. It is made to mock all these other free-to-play games that, under the technicality of the term, are free to play, but cannot be played effectively without buying some DLC starter pack. Of course, in this game, you don't actually have to use real money to purchase any of the DLC. The currency you use is the in-game coins, so all you will pay for the game is the initial purchase price. It even comes with a DLC Expansion of the story: Live Freemium or DIE!. Overall, this game is worth the price, even if it is a little shorter than it could have been."
