,Recommended,230050,24720906,"Posted: 5 August, 2016",all,Ghgore,"Are you tired of buying tons of DLC to get the full experienceoit of your AAA games?Though this game can't change EA's marketing strategies, it can provide hours of humorous, satirical fun, and a few achievements for your inner achievement hunter.Gameplay:Overall pretty fun, as the platforming aspects range pretty easy (not too easy as to not be fun though), to hard enough that it might take me a few tries, but not hard enough to rage quit.Controls:The default keyboard controls are fine, as it uses a two handed system as in, you use Z and X with your left hand and the arrow keys with your right. You can always change this through the settings menu though. My Xbox 360 controller also worked well, and I would recommend using it over the keyboard, since you get the added comfort, and you don't lose any precision or actions since there's only two controls besides movement anyway.Story:This game doesn't really have much story, but at the same time, it's not really necessary, as the main pointof the game is to be satire against companies like EA, Activision, and pretty much every AAA publisher for their ridiculous amounts of DLC. The little story it does have is quite hilarious (as again the game is satire), and it's worth the $2.99 fir the humor.Final Thoughts:This game is a short satire game, making fun of a huge problem in the AAA game industry, and for it's small price tag, it's entirely worth the purchase, especially if it's on sale."
