,Recommended,230050,11487260,"Posted: 30 July, 2014",all,viad,"DLC Quest is a satire of recent trends in the video game industry (based on the game's release) where companies are forcing more and more DLC and microtransactions on the players. Thus, this game is based more on its message and theme rather than giving a solid gameplay experience with story and impresssive design.This game takes a somewhat retro graphical style mixed with a typical fantasy theme. The music is made up of chiptune tracks to fit in with the retro visuals. The story is as simple as saving a princess or saving a village from a bad guy, which are commonly seen in other games that aren't parodic in nature. These things though are the not very important parts to be looking for in this game. They get the job done by looking good enough from a technical standpoint to drive the game, since these three things are parodies of commonly seen styles and tropes in other games.Even though this game is a parody and satire of video games, there is some actual gameplay to be had. The player runs and jumps to collect coins and somethimes kill things in this platformer game. To unlock new ""features"", the player needs to spend their coins on DLC and microtransactions, somewhat mirroring the real world with exaggerations. The gameplay ranges from easy in the first episode to a sightly more difficult, but not hard difficulty in the second episode.Does the game satirize the video game industry well? It does do so in a blunt, exaggerated manner which ends up being silly game expansions the player has to buy. If the game isn't poking fun at video game companies, it then has parodies of games, ranging from making fun of certain game genre conventions to referencing specific video games. Not all the humor will leave people laughing out loud, but it should give a small laugh or chuckle for the things DLC Quest parodies.DLC Quest should be taken as a game with a message, and it does bring some silliness when it comes to parodying the games industry. This game is definitely short, easy, and low priced, which should give a decent amount of time for the money. With a satirical and comical approach to DLC and microtransactions, this game is great for the humor along with decent platforming collectathon gameplay on the side."
