76561197974877837,Not Recommended,230050,7758837,"Posted: 25 November, 2013",all,Spalls Hurgenson,"An amusing riff on publishers' attempt to over-monetize their titles contrary to the actual artistry of the title. DLC Quest is a one-joke game, but it's a funny joke and it fortunately knows when to let it go. It succeeds where other similar satires fail (I'm looking at you, 2004 Bard's Tale!) because rather than drag on and on trying to milk that single joke into a full-length game, DLC Quest is - wisely - a very short experience As in, less than an hour long to get to the end. As such, it is barely worth it's price, especially since the gameplay is that of an uninspired platformer. Still, it's rare that a game gets me to crack an honest smile so even if it does seem a bit overpriced, I'll forgive it because it actually was funny."
