,Not Recommended,230050,13164614,"Posted: 30 November, 2014",all,Dowlphwin,"Some mild spoilers ahead (if that's even a thing with this game, haha.)Skippable intro screen, super-fast, no-fuss menu navigation, support for very high resolutions. The first impression of the technical side of this game is pleasant.The humor suffers a good bit from the fact that the game pokes fun at itself in such an in-your-face way, not hinting, but more like telling a joke and announcing when the punchline will come and what it is about. The kind of 'humor' that can sometimes sound more like a sarcastic rant. An NPC saying stuff like ""I'm a filler NPC. I have no purpose."" isn't really funny. Those things make the game look more like an interactive critical essay.The gameplay logic is more interesting, because it depicts the design flaw of the illusion of choice in an extremely streamlined progression well.The music is not bad.So the game itself is mediocre at best AND it is so short that after having bought it for 1 EUR, which is 67% off, I feel that's a bit too much.It has two 'campaigns'. (Not sure whether that was originally the case.) The first one I played through in a bit less than an hour. The second one in 1.2 hours, not with all achievements though.Some times I came up with better dialogues while playing because they leave so much to be desired. But some dialogue and gameplay is OK; It's not all lackluster. It's just overall an extremely mediocre experience; nothing memorable.The best thing is, as I mentioned, the speedy menu navigation, and the equally crisp and fun controls."
