,Not Recommended,230050,8009216,"Posted: 11 December, 2013",all,ALTUS PRIME,"What is there to say about this game? For starters it's less of a game than it is a walking parody of (modern) gaming and its tropes, with some platforming and light puzzle solving / fetch quests sprinkled in. There's a horse armor joke. There are hats to collect. Yes, there's even a Markus ""Notch"" Persson reference involving a pickaxe.The humor is strongest during the game's first ""campaign"", which can be finished in 30 minutes to over an hour depending on your playstyle. After that, any charm DLC Quest had evaporates, as its slightly novel gameplay becomes a grind in order to progress. Full disclosure: it has been some time since I've played my copy, and there may be some things I'm misremembering or skipping altogether. But the feeling remains with me: this game did not need a second half.Should you buy DLC Quest? For the price, it is hardly something to fret over. You could spend $2.99 on -ACTUAL- DLC and be more disappointed. But because the jokes are so easy, and the fact that it's just repackaged internet humor, prevents me from fully endorsing this title."
