,Not Recommended,230050,10666296,"Posted: 22 June, 2014",all,frenchiefellow,"I find it hard to recommend this game, as I find very few redeemable qualities in this game, other than its very small price tag (although, arguably, its a little high unless its on sale; I got it for ~$0.89). Normally, I'm not a big fan of platformers, nor retro ones at that unless it has something enticing to it (a tie to another series, perhaps), but at the low price tag, I decided to try it out. Basically, this is a standard platformer with a satirical twist; You have to purchase DLC (in game, with in game currency) to proceed or do most of the actions of the game. Now sure this is funny at first, but after going back and forth to collect coins to buy DLC to progess (you need like 3-4 of them to ""win"") in a ""story"" that would otherwise take 2-3 minutes is more annoying than funny after a few minutes. There are a few little chuckles to be found with some of the NPC dialouge, but nothing to go out of your way to find. This game should take you no more than 30-45 minutes to complete (perhaps multiple times) and most likely 100% it, and even that is probably more than a generous estimation. There are two game modes, but I was offput enough from the first to forgo the second.  Unless you really really really enjoy platformers or you need an excuse to waste $2 and 30 minutes, I'm going to say stay clear. 3/10"
