,Recommended,230050,11026497,"Posted: 2 July, 2014",all,Apple Zombie,"For a small price and even smaller on sale (74cents for me) you can experience an indie developers take on the state of the gaming industry. You'll find the game make fun of most forms of DLC and the sad thing is, though a bit exaggerated, the game does make some fair points.The game play is pretty simple, but the controls are fluid and responsive. You essentially play a hero on a quest to collect coins to purchase in-game DLC, ranging from character animations to ad-removals. The story is goofy, but with a meaningful message underneath. Personally I found the humor in the game rather entertaining, a lot of nerd references are used in the game, so some jokes my go over people's head.Be warned that the game is very short and most people will probably beat it in a single sitting, maybe two. Took me about 1 and half hours to get through both campaigns, but it can be done even faster for an achievement. I personally think the game was a great way to pass a couple of hours for less than a dollar. You won't find a whole lot of content, but plenty of DLC."
