,Not Recommended,230050,18946275,"Posted: 7 November, 2015",all,ProxyLou,"DLC Quest is a shallow experience not any more entertaining than the games it sets out to criticize. What little it does have to offer are boring and simple obersavtions in the gaming industry that any one could have told you for free. The gameplay is as basic and uninspired as its sense of humor, bringing nothing new to the platforming genre. Both campaigns are at their core, the exact same game, but with a new skin.A game is not absolved of having bad design just because it critizes other games for having bad design. Just because the game presents a generic 'captured-princess' story while saying, ""isn't this generic?"" doesn't make it excusable. Its laziness, and makes the game appear to be as bad of a timely cash-grab as the DLC it wants to comment on.As a platformer, it fails to entertain. As a time-piece, it fails to provoke thought. With all that considered, what could this game have to offer? Nothing. A good example of the poor ""what did you expect from a $3 indie game?"" excuse."
