,Recommended,230050,3135004,"Posted: 20 March, 2013",all,downphoenix,"Decent but short game. It definitely paints a grim picture of what we might see in games that are microtransaction based in the future. This game is more of an intellectual game and less of a game you'd play for fun, as the gameplay is pretty tedious. This is intentional design to drive home what the average DLC/Microtransaction ridden game is like, often times they dont add any real new content but just adds to the grind. For instance, there's one DLC pack you purchase to use a grindstone at 1000x capacity. So either you hit the X button a few times or thousands if you dont buy it.I dont recommend this for people that just want a simple and fun platformer, I recommend it for people that want to be aware of what some game companies may actually do in the industry in the future."
