,Recommended,230050,16801128,"Posted: 29 June, 2015",all,B Sharp Major General,"*Minor spoilers ahead*DLC Quest is a biting, savvy satire on modern gaming practice. Want to jump? You'll need to buy it. Want to pause or go left? You'll need to buy that too! There's even an entire section that's ""unfinished"" when you first arrive at it.*End spoilers*Despite being a short game, DLC Quest is a solid title. The controls are tight, and the gameplay isn't overly repetitive. Dialogue and level design are creative and humourous. There's nods and jabs at other indie and AAA titles spread throughout the game.Both DLC Quest and Live Freemium or Die are worth the price. With its price less than $5, DLC Quest is definitely a game worth playing.I give this game my obfuscating rank of Ab / Major Scale"
