,Recommended,230050,10072981,"Posted: 10 May, 2014",all,Captain Picco,"DLC quest is an indie title developed by GoingLoud which uses satire based around the current state of video game development and the monetisation of additional or in some cases ""cut"" content for titles.Gameplay- 2D sidescrolling platformer similar to titles such as Super Mario Bros.- New abilities are unlocked by purchasing DLC (done with in-game money).Visuals- 16-bit retro style graphics- Colourful landscapesSound- Retro soundtrack which fits well with the titles art style- Varied music which changes as the player progresses to each new areaExtras- Steam version comes with additional campaign ""Live Freemium or Die""- 20 awardments to unlock in-game and 22 steam achievements to unlock (20 based on the awardments, 2 hidden)Overall, the title is fun to play and contains a lot of references which many members of the gaming culture will understand. Both campaigns are short in length and can be completed within one sitting but if you want to play a cheap fun little title then I recommend you give DLC quest a go.Score - 7.5/10"
