,Recommended,230050,11007845,"Posted: 1 July, 2014",all,\[T]/,"A pretty enjoyable game to while away an afternoon. Actually, not even that long sadly.Its always nice to see a game delivering social commentary, but the main game was so incredibly easy that it felt pandering (I've yet to play the second part). And I'm not even into platformers all that much, I'd feel sorry for an SMB fan that stumbled on this. The difficulty isn't the purpose of the game I guess, but at the same time its pointless to satirise one aspect of the development process if by doing so you damage a different aspect. A good example is the second ending, a prime opportunity for a boss fight, what should be the epitome of the game, and yeah, it sucked. I restarted the game for a short, pretty lousy, cutscene. Yay. Maybe this was an artistic decision, maybe I was supposed to be let down by the second ending DLC. Well, in reality I was let down by the game itself.I suppose I come off as a harsh critic; I did genuinely, briefly, enjoy the game and appreciated what it set out to accomplish. It just grew tedious from the lack of challenge is all. I suppose the game's generous pricetag, especially during sales, cover for it to a degree. But only to a degree."
