,Recommended,230050,7911382,"Posted: 4 December, 2013",all,CaptainTempest,"DLC Quest isn't so much a game as it is a parody. That said, it's a quirky and satirical journey across two small campaigns packed with jokes and references that poke fun at the all too familiar concepts of downloadable content, pay-to-play, preorder exclusives, and freemium. The campaigns themselves are very, VERY short, myself finishing both of them and clocking in at about 2.5 hours, but this game isn't meant to be a huge adventure. Despite the length, its got a decent amount of humor put into it, and the platformer mechanics and gameplay are simple enough for anyone to pick up. Good for the two hours I spent, granted I also acquired it on sale for $0.98. If you're looking to kill a few hours with something simple and witty, then this is a game I would consider."
