,Not Recommended,230050,10733092,"Posted: 23 June, 2014",all,rizefall,"DLC Quest is a very simple platformer which really does nothing new, fun or engaging when it comes to its Gameplay but that’s probably not the reason anyone buys this to begin with.The game makes fun of how DLC works today (and also takes it to the extreme). Want animations? Do you want to jump up those blocks? Then you got to pay gold (money earned in-game) and that’s how the game works. You control your character going around the game collecting gold to buy new DLC so you are able to make progress. Most of the DLCs you buy are pretty funny and if you have ever had problems with DLC, heard or read of the controversies it has spawned then you are in for a laugh. Other than that there is nothing more to it. You jump around, collect coins and use a small sword for mostly cutting grass.The game has two campaigns, the original which is “DLC Quest” which I recommend the most because it’s short and is the most fun out of the two in my opinion.  The second is “Live Freemium or Die” is kind of like the sequel to the first game and it’s more of the same fun DLC missions (It extends the story, many more missions and stuff to do). I had a hard time going through it though mostly because I got stuck a few times and because you have to do more Platforming which is not that fun in this game to begin with. If you laughed through the first campaign like me you will probably go through it at least once but it was too long and trying to be too serious for its own good. I play a game for it's good gameplay and it's not something that DLC quest has. Id say play it if you want a few laughs but not if you want a good gameplay experience."
