,Recommended,230050,1981989,"Posted: 27 June, 2013",all,Joseph Hicks,"DLC Quest, as the name implies, mocks the controversial practices and... liberties some companies take (and have taken) with the system since it's inception. The game is pretty straightforward - actually, it's so short and everything is so simple it feels like a very long (but still funny) joke. Comes with two campaigns. The first, the original ""DLC Quest"", feels kind of dull now, but I can see it being pretty funny when the whole DLC craze started; the second, ""Live Freemium or Die"" DID make me laugh. This seocnd one is more recent - including jokes that go all the way through Skyrim and to Deus Ex: Human Revolution.Treat the first campaign as a tutorial and have a blast with the second.The game is really simple, and I like to think that it's part of the joke. The game is really short - about half of the length of the original Portal, considering both campaigns. Well, for two bucks, it's worth it."
,Recommended,230050,2726999,"Posted: 21 July, 2013",all,Sunshine,"Super fun! Not a ton of replay value, but has some good humor and is entertaining."
,Recommended,230050,7437355,"Posted: 20 October, 2013",all,Sci_Karate,"""What happens when DLC goes to far?Basic features are now DLC! Animation? DLC! Pausing the game? DLC! Moving to the left? Well, tha'ts included. No, it's not! DLC!""- DLC Quest trailerDLC Quest is an open-world side-scrolling DLC-em-up.Upon starting the game, you can only move right. Nothing else. You collect coins as you move, and eventually bump into a shopkeeper. From him, you can buy the ability to move left. Then, later, you can buy: jumping, weapons, pause menus, and more!DLC Quest is much less an actual game than it is a hilarious satire.For anyone and everyone who thinks that fifteen-dollar map packs and four-dollar weapon skins in modern video games are ridiculous, play DLC Quest, and laugh with me. It's not very long, but then again: It's only three dollars.$3/1.9 hours = $1.58/hour.As a game: 6.5/10As a satire: 9.75/10Final Score: 8.13/10Letter Grade: B-Money/Playtime: $1.58/hour"
