,Recommended,230050,11082687,"Posted: 5 July, 2014",all,MacMillan,"DLC Quest is a fantastic platformer game that mocks all the DLCs in today's gaming industry.Basically you must buy lots and lots of DLCs (with in-game coins) to make any progress. These include a DLC that adds the action of moving left and jumping, a DLC that gives your character a useless top hat, a DLC that fixes a bug that could have been fixed before game release, a DLC that adds a useless NPC, a DLC that gives the chance to change your name once, a DLC that shows a health bar...Besides the idea of buying DLCs, the game itself is well-made. The control feels fluent, and the graphic and soundtrack combine to produce an 8-bit oldschool style. And the final boss battle is creative. I'll not spoil it here, but it also involves DLC, and is fought in a way I've never seen before.+ a game about games+ fluent control+ oldschool graphic and sound+ humor- 1st campaign is too short- would be better if the Map DLC actually gives a map9 out of 10, marvelous."
