,Recommended,230050,8385967,"Posted: 28 December, 2013",all,Dasyati,"Takes less than 2 hours to 100% both campaigns, as you can see from the screenshot of the leaderboard.  A lot of that is going back and forth across the map between the next trigger and the nearest shopkeeper so you can buy the next DLC that suddenly becomes available to advance the story.On the bright side, the whole game isn't long enough for the back-and-forth to really become grating.  The game itself isn't exactly difficult either; the only boss battle in the entire game is nearly impossible to fail, and you can't even die until part 2.  The point of the game is not to be challenging, but to tell a few jokes and mock DLC-laden AAA games (andone indie developer).  In that sense it feels like it would be more at home on Kongregate than on XBLIG or Steam.All in all, worth about a dollar.  Get it when it's on sale."
