,Recommended,230050,33295057,Posted: 5 July,all,Sorceror Nobody,"This game is an amusing romp through the world of DLC gone rogue, and it's quite enjoyable. It pokes fun at all the tropes you'd expect, and does it quite well. For a couple of quid, it's a decent game, and for that reason, I recommend it.There is a but, though. It does its thing quite well,but, perhaps too well, as I'll explain in a second. The first campaign, plain old DLC Quest, is fine. You can finish it in 30-40 minutes without overly rushing, and it's enjoyable for that time. But let me tell you a tale of Live Freemium or Die. That turned into, for me, an hour long play session that remained funny, but stopped being fun. The primary issue is that the second campaign plays on the Fetch Quest trope a little too well, and starts to run the joke into the ground pretty quickly. It's making a point, and I get that, but I'm sure there must have been a way to make that point without making the game quite such a tedious pain in the backtracking butt.The tl;dr of this review is that the game is generally fun and worth the entry price...You should just know what you're in for on the second campaign."
